    "fn_id": "senkaku_diaoyu_islands",
    "note": "MERGED atomic: absorbs east_china_sea_claims (spec 2 A2b -- Senkaku 12 / ECS 5 / both 1 / shelf-gas 1 titles per 180d; not splittable, no centroid to target for 'the East China Sea'). Dyad gate centroid_ids={ASIA-CHINA} + primary_target=ASIA-JAPAN makes the domain nouns (coast guard, EEZ, buoy) safe. DROPPED pre-audit: bare 'rig' (EN word-START anchor -> matches 'rights'), bare zh 'diaoyu' equivalent 钓鱼 (= 'fishing'; use 钓鱼岛), 'drill'/'exercise' (belongs to japan_defense_expansion), 'Taisho' (= wartime military rank / era name, not the islet). DROPPED post-audit (real-gate check, not %foreign): 'intrusion' 13 titles of which 12 were the GSDF embassy knife incident, 'intrude' 6/6 embassy, 'patrol' 8/9 either China-patrols-near-Taiwan or China-Russia bomber patrols. All three belong to other atomics; the one real Diaoyu patrol title also carries 'Diaoyu' + 'coast guard', so recall loss is zero. Kept 'fishing boat' (13/13 genuine EEZ seizures)."
